-- Former MVP Nowitzki Out at Least Six Weeks After Knee Surgery
-- B y   J a y   B e b e r m a n
-- 2012-10-19T17:02:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-19/former-mvp-nowitzki-out-at-least-six-weeks-after-knee-surgery.html
Dallas  Mavericks forward Dirk
Nowitzki, a former league most valuable player and an 11-time
All-Star, will be out at least six weeks after undergoing
surgery on his right knee, the National Basketball Association
team said in a statement.  Nowitzki, 34, has averaged 22.9 points and 6.8 rebounds
during his 14-year career. He led Dallas to the title after the
2010-11 season and won the MVP in 2007.  The Mavericks begin the season Oct. 30 in Los Angeles
against the Lakers.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jay Beberman at 
 jbeberman@bloomberg.net  